  "ciliary_role": "Ezrin, ELMO-DOCK1 and its downstream effector Rac1 cooperate and function as a module during the highly coordi ted processes of ciliary basal body targeting and docking to the apical membrane. Co-immunostainings with Cep164 confirmed that DOCK1 localised to both mother and daughter centrioles.(25516973). loss of WDR-31 together with RP-2 and ELMD-1 (the sole ortholog ELMOD1-3) results in ciliary accumulations of IFT Complex B components and KIF17 kinesin, with fewer IFT/BBSome particles traveling along cilia in both anterograde and retrograde directions, suggesting that the IFT/BBSome entry into the cilia and exit from the cilia are impacted , WDR31-RP-2-ELMD-1 as IFT and BBSome trafficking regulators(37208194).",
